The Bill of Materials tab defines those products that are generated from other products. A Bill of Material (BOM) is one or more Products or BOMs.
Available Quantity: - Stored BOMs have to be created via "Production" - The available quantity of a non-stored BOMs is dynamically calculated - The attribute "Stored" is defined in the "Product" tab
Price: - BOMs must be listed in Pricelists - If the price is 0.00, the price is dynamically calculated
Printing: - Usually, only the BOM information is printed - For invoices, delivery slips and pick lists, you have the option to print the details - In the details, the quantity is listed - and the price, if this is dynamically calculated

There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.

Document sequence number of the document

The document number is usually automatically generated by the system and determined by the document type of the document. If the document is not saved, the preliminary number is displayed in "<>".
If the document type of your document has no automatic document sequence defined, the field is empty if you create a new document. This is for documents which usually have an external number (like vendor invoice). If you leave the field empty, the system will generate a document number for you. The document sequence used for this fallback number is defined in the "Maintain Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table (e.g. C_Order).

PO.Data:
La pestaña lista de materiales define aquellos productos que son generados desde otros producdtos. Una Lista de Materiales (LDM) es uno o más productos o LDMs.
Cantidad Disponible: - LDM Almacenados deben ser creados via "Producción" - La cantidad disponible de un LDM no almacenado es calculada dinámicamente - El atributo "Almacenado" es definido en la pestaña de "Producto"
Precio: - Las LDMs deben ser listadas en las listas de precios - Si el precio es 0.00, entonces es calculado dinámicamente
Imprimiendo: - Usualmente, solo la información de LDM es impresa - Para facturas, listas de despacho y listas de empaque, tiene la opción de imprimir los detalles - En los detalles, la cantidad es listada - y el precio, si es calculado dinámicamente
